    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.5.33" />
                
                <note place="top" type="curatorial">209 Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">33</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">DAVID STARR JORDAN
                        <lb/>
                    STANFORD UNIVERSITY <add>P.O.</add>
                        <lb/>
                    CALIFORNIA</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>     
                    <dateline>November 15th,1918.</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                
                            <addrLine>Bancroft, Nebraska.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I thank you for your very kind, helpful and hopeful letter. As Gambetta once observed: "When danger is past, trouble begins",and we shall have more or less difficulty with the wild democrats of Central Europe, as well as with the hard-faced aristocrats in our own country.</p>
                
                <p>I am interested in your problems, and also in the probability that the <add>"</add>Three Friends<add>"</add> will appear pretty soon. You will also soon receive a little book of mine on democracy.</p>
                
                <p>I have written a little booklet,which I will send you as soon as I get some more copies, on "The Root of the Evil". Our Government has ordered 80,000 of them and sent a man to Europe to distribute them among German prisoners in England and France.</p>
                
                <p>I am interested in your experience with the <hi rend="underline">Minneapolis Journal</hi>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With best wishes,  I am,</salute>
                    <salute>Very sincerely yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>David Starr J<del>ordan</del>,</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
